                            <comment id="17868751" author="dcapwell" created="Thu, 25 Jul 2024 18:05:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Linking &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19279&quot; title=&quot;Test Failure: org.apache.cassandra.simulator.test.HarrySimulatorTest&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19279&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19279&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as this patch fixes it.  Looks like direct memory is undersized for simulation for some reason, so I fixed the JVM configs and now Harry is no longer failing that way... &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17868805" author="dcapwell" created="Thu, 25 Jul 2024 21:15:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Simulator now passes far more often in CI (passes for me 90% of the time).  It is flakey and thats due to a bug that &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ifesdjeen&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ifesdjeen&quot;&gt;ifesdjeen&lt;/a&gt; is looking into (NPE in TCM)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
